{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XQUMkGpuUiPf6eYq4Um4nY","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have everything I need. Let me create a comprehensive report.\n\n## Comprehensive E2E Test Setup & Environment Configuration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the E2E test infrastructure, environment configuration, and env var consumption. Here's the complete picture:\n\n---\n\n## 1. **Playwright Configuration Files**\n\n### `playwright.local.config.ts`\n- **Purpose**: Local E2E integration tests against a local `solana-test-validator`\n- **Port**: 3002\n- **Test pattern**: `local/**/*.spec.ts`\n- **Key env vars injected into webServer**:\n  - `VITE_MOCK_MODE=false` (real wallet mode)\n  - `VITE_TEST_WALLET=true` (test wallet mode)\n  - `VITE_RPC_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8899` (local validator)\n  - `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK=localnet`\n- **Features**: Single worker, 60s timeout, trace retained on failure\n\n### `playwright.real.config.ts`\n- **Purpose**: Real wallet mode tests against devnet\n- **Port**: 3001\n- **Test pattern**: `real/**/*.spec.ts`\n- **Key env vars**:\n  - `VITE_MOCK_MODE=false`\n  - `VITE_RPC_URL=https://api.devnet.solana.com`\n\n### `playwright.config.ts` (Visual/default)\n- **Purpose**: Visual regression and component tests\n- **Port**: 3000\n- **Test pattern**: `visual/**/*.spec.ts`\n- **Key env vars**:\n  - `VITE_MOCK_MODE=true` (mock wallet)\n\n---\n\n## 2. **All VITE_ Environment Variables Currently Used**\n\n| Env Var | Purpose | Used By | Default | Examples |\n|---------|---------|---------|---------|----------|\n| `VITE_MOCK_MODE` | Controls wallet provider branch (mock vs real) | `WalletProvider.tsx` | `\"false\"` (real mode) | `\"true\"` \\| `\"false\"` |\n| `VITE_TEST_WALLET` | Enables test wallet with injected keypair seed | `WalletProvider.tsx` | `\"false\"` | `\"true\"` \\| `\"false\"` |\n| `VITE_RPC_URL` | Solana RPC endpoint URL | `WalletProvider.tsx`, `TestWalletWrapper.tsx` | `https://api.devnet.solana.com` | `http://127.0.0.1:8899`, `https://api.devnet.solana.com` |\n| `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK` | Solana cluster name (for wallet-adapter) | `RealWalletProvider.tsx` | `\"devnet\"` | `\"devnet\"` \\| `\"testnet\"` \\| `\"mainnet-beta\"` |\n| `VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID` | Coinflip program address override | `chain.ts`, `verification.ts` | *(from IDL)* | `BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx` |\n| `VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID` | Platform program address override | `chain.ts` (claimPayout) | `85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA` | *(varies per deployment)* |\n\n---\n\n## 3. **Program ID Resolution Strategy**\n\n### **Source Hierarchy**\n1. **VITE_ env vars take precedence** (if set)\n2. **IDL embedded defaults fallback** (if env var not provided)\n\n### **IDL Locations**\n- **Coinflip**: `@rng-utopia/anchor-client` exports `CoinflipIDL` (from `coinflip.json`)\n- **Platform**: `@rng-utopia/anchor-client` exports `PlatformIDL` (from `platform.json`)\n\n### **Code Patterns**\n```typescript\n// chain.ts, line 20-22\nconst COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  import.meta.env.VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID ?? CoinflipIDL.address\n);\n\n// chain.ts, line 445-448\nconst PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  import.meta.env.VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID ?? \n  \"85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA\"\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. **E2E Test Fixtures & Helpers Structure**\n\n### **Dual-Browser Context Fixture** (`e2e/local/fixtures.ts`)\n```typescript\nexport interface DualPlayerFixtures {\n  playerAContext: BrowserContext;          // Player A's isolated browser context\n  playerBContext: BrowserContext;          // Player B's isolated browser context\n  playerAPage: Page;                       // Page in player A's context\n  playerBPage: Page;                       // Page in player B's context\n  playerAKeypair: Keypair;                 // PLAYER_A (from wallets.ts)\n  playerBKeypair: Keypair;                 // PLAYER_B (from wallets.ts)\n  connection: Connection;                  // Shared RPC connection\n}\n```\n\n**Key mechanism**: Uses `addInitScript` to inject `window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__` before page load, allowing `TestWalletWrapper` to construct the correct keypair.\n\n### **Wallet Keypairs** (`e2e/local/helpers/wallets.ts`)\n```typescript\nconst SEED_PLAYER_A = new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xaa);  // Deterministic\nconst SEED_PLAYER_B = new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xbb);  // Deterministic\n\nexport const PLAYER_A = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_PLAYER_A);\nexport const PLAYER_B = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_PLAYER_B);\nexport const LOCAL_RPC_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\";\n\n// Helper to fund wallets (idempotent)\nexport async function fundTestWallets(rpcUrl, solAmount): Promise<{ \n  playerA: Keypair; \n  playerB: Keypair; \n  connection: Connection \n}>;\n```\n\n### **On-Chain Helpers** (`e2e/local/helpers/on-chain.ts`)\n**Program ID resolution**:\n```typescript\nexport const COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(CoinflipIDL.address);\nexport const PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(PlatformIDL.address);\n```\n\n**Account types & interfaces**:\n- `MatchAccount` — deserialized coinflip match PDA\n- `PlayerProfileAccount` — deserialized player profile PDA\n\n**Assertion helpers**:\n- `assertMatchCreated(connection, creator, expectedTier, expectedSide)`\n- `assertMatchClosed(connection, matchPda)`\n- `assertTreasuryFee(connection, treasury, balanceBefore, entryAmount)`\n- `assertPlayerProfile(connection, wallet, expected)`\n- `assertPlayerProfileDelta(connection, wallet, before, delta)`\n\n**Balance & snapshot helpers**:\n- `snapshotBalance(connection, address)` — capture SOL balance\n- `snapshotPlayerProfile(connection, wallet)` — capture profile stats (returns zeros if not exists)\n- `calculateExpectedFee(entryAmount)` — mirrors on-chain fee logic: `fee = floor(pool * 300 / 10_000)`\n\n### **Localnet Setup** (`e2e/local/helpers/localnet-setup.ts`)\n```typescript\n// Deterministic admin & treasury keypairs\nconst ADMIN = Keypair.fromSeed(new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xdd));\nconst TREASURY = Keypair.fromSeed(new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xcc));\n\n// Initializes both program configs (idempotent)\nexport async function initializeLocalnet(rpcUrl = LOCAL_RPC_URL): Promise<void>;\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. **`.env` Files**\n\n### `.env.devnet` (Current)\n```\nVITE_RPC_URL=https://api.devnet.solana.com\nVITE_SOLANA_NETWORK=devnet\nVITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID=BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\nVITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID=85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA\n```\n\n### `.env.example`\n```\n# Wallet Mode\n# VITE_MOCK_MODE=true\n\n# Solana Configuration\nVITE_RPC_URL=https://api.devnet.solana.com\nVITE_SOLANA_NETWORK=devnet\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. **Vite Configuration** (`vite.config.ts`)\n- **Default port**: 3000\n- **Server host**: `true` (accessible from non-localhost)\n- **Build optimizations**: Manual chunks for react/solana vendor splitting\n- **No special env var handling** — relies on Vite's automatic `VITE_*` exposure\n\n---\n\n## 7. **WalletProvider Initialization Flow**\n\n### **Decision Tree**\n```\nVITE_MOCK_MODE === \"true\"\n  ├─ Yes → MockWalletProvider (no RPC interaction)\n  └─ No\n      ├─ VITE_TEST_WALLET === \"true\"\n      │   └─ TestWalletWrapper (reads window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__)\n      └─ No → RealWalletProvider (UnifiedWallet modal)\n```\n\n### **RPC URL Resolution** (`getRpcUrl()`)\n```typescript\nconst envUrl = import.meta.env?.VITE_RPC_URL ?? undefined;\nreturn envUrl || DEFAULT_RPC_URL;  // DEFAULT_RPC_URL = \"https://api.devnet.solana.com\"\n```\n\n### **Network/Cluster Resolution** (`getCluster()`)\n```typescript\nconst network = import.meta.env?.VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK;\nif (network === \"mainnet-beta\" || network === \"testnet\") return network;\nreturn \"devnet\";  // Default to devnet\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. **Test Wallet System**\n\n### **Flow for E2E Tests**\n1. **Playwright injects keypair seed** via `addInitScript` → `window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__`\n2. **WalletProvider detects** `VITE_TEST_WALLET=true` and renders `TestWalletWrapper`\n3. **TestWalletWrapper reads** `window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__` and creates keypair\n4. **TestWalletProvider** wraps the keypair with signing capability\n5. **Frontend can sign transactions** without modal prompts\n\n### **Key Code** (`test/TestWalletWrapper.tsx`)\n```typescript\nconst keypair = Keypair.fromSeed(new Uint8Array(seed));\nconst rpcUrl = import.meta.env?.VITE_RPC_URL as string | undefined;\nreturn <TestWalletProvider keypair={keypair} rpcUrl={rpcUrl || undefined}>{children}</TestWalletProvider>;\n```\n\n---\n\n## 9. **Visual Regression Setup** (`fixtures.ts` at root of `e2e/`)\n\n**Key fixture**: `stablePage` extends Playwright's test:\n- **Deterministic randomness** via seeded Mulberry32 PRNG (seed=42)\n- **Frozen Date.now()** to 2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\n- **Disabled CSS/SVG animations** to ensure pixel-perfect snapshots\n- **Console error detection** — fails test if errors logged\n- **Network idle enforcement** — waits for all requests to settle\n\n---\n\n## 10. **Summary: What You Need for Devnet Validation Module**\n\n### **Environment Variables to Validate**\n1. `VITE_RPC_URL` — must be reachable, valid HTTPS/HTTP URL\n2. `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK` — must be one of: `devnet` | `testnet` | `mainnet-beta`\n3. `VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID` — must be a valid Solana address (58 chars, base58)\n4. `VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID` — must be a valid Solana address\n\n### **On-Chain Validation to Implement**\n1. **RPC health check** — `connection.getHealth()` or `getLatestBlockhash()`\n2. **Program deployment check** — fetch program account at `VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID` and `VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID`\n3. **Keypoint config check** — verify coinflip & platform configs initialized (PDAs derivable)\n4. **Treasury check** — treasury wallet set and accessible\n\n### **Fallback Chain**\n- Program IDs: VITE_ env vars → IDL embedded defaults\n- RPC URL: VITE_RPC_URL → `https://api.devnet.solana.com`\n- Network: VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK → `devnet`\n\n---\n\n## File Paths (Absolute)\n\n1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.local.config.ts` — Local E2E config\n2. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/.env.devnet` — Devnet env file\n3. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts` — Visual regression fixture\n4. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/fixtures.ts` — Dual-player fixture\n5. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/wallets.ts` — Wallet setup\n6. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/on-chain.ts` — On-chain helpers\n7. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/localnet-setup.ts` — Localnet init\n8. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/vite.config.ts` — Vite build config\n9. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/WalletProvider.tsx` — Wallet provider root\n10. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/test/TestWalletWrapper.tsx` — Test wallet wrapper\n11. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/real/RealWalletProvider.tsx` — Real wallet provider\n12. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` — Program ID and on-chain logic\n13. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/verification.ts` — Fairness verification"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a58a7691f73942e6a (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 60589\ntool_uses: 37\nduration_ms: 85743</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6dadced6-465c-4292-ac5d-45e74b91a9b8","uuid":"f35e21d2-c050-431a-9bf2-5bf2999a4eb6","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the existing E2E test setup and environment configuration for a devnet E2E test environment. Please explore:\n\n1. `apps/platform/playwright.local.config.ts` - the local E2E config (I'll model devnet after this)\n2. `apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/wallets.ts` - wallet setup pattern\n3. `apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/on-chain.ts` - on-chain helpers that derive program IDs\n4. `apps/platform/e2e/local/fixtures.ts` - the test fixtures\n5. Any existing `.env` files or env configuration in `apps/platform/` (check `.env`, `.env.local`, `.env.example`, `.env.devnet`, etc.)\n6. `apps/platform/vite.config.ts` or similar to see how env vars are consumed\n7. Check `apps/platform/src/` for any existing `VITE_*` env var references related to RPC, program IDs, VRF config\n\nBe thorough - I need to know all VITE_ env vars currently used and how program IDs are sourced (from IDL? from env?). The goal is to create a devnet env validation module.\n\nWorking directory: /workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia","agentId":"a58a7691f73942e6a","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have everything I need. Let me create a comprehensive report.\n\n## Comprehensive E2E Test Setup & Environment Configuration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the E2E test infrastructure, environment configuration, and env var consumption. Here's the complete picture:\n\n---\n\n## 1. **Playwright Configuration Files**\n\n### `playwright.local.config.ts`\n- **Purpose**: Local E2E integration tests against a local `solana-test-validator`\n- **Port**: 3002\n- **Test pattern**: `local/**/*.spec.ts`\n- **Key env vars injected into webServer**:\n  - `VITE_MOCK_MODE=false` (real wallet mode)\n  - `VITE_TEST_WALLET=true` (test wallet mode)\n  - `VITE_RPC_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8899` (local validator)\n  - `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK=localnet`\n- **Features**: Single worker, 60s timeout, trace retained on failure\n\n### `playwright.real.config.ts`\n- **Purpose**: Real wallet mode tests against devnet\n- **Port**: 3001\n- **Test pattern**: `real/**/*.spec.ts`\n- **Key env vars**:\n  - `VITE_MOCK_MODE=false`\n  - `VITE_RPC_URL=https://api.devnet.solana.com`\n\n### `playwright.config.ts` (Visual/default)\n- **Purpose**: Visual regression and component tests\n- **Port**: 3000\n- **Test pattern**: `visual/**/*.spec.ts`\n- **Key env vars**:\n  - `VITE_MOCK_MODE=true` (mock wallet)\n\n---\n\n## 2. **All VITE_ Environment Variables Currently Used**\n\n| Env Var | Purpose | Used By | Default | Examples |\n|---------|---------|---------|---------|----------|\n| `VITE_MOCK_MODE` | Controls wallet provider branch (mock vs real) | `WalletProvider.tsx` | `\"false\"` (real mode) | `\"true\"` \\| `\"false\"` |\n| `VITE_TEST_WALLET` | Enables test wallet with injected keypair seed | `WalletProvider.tsx` | `\"false\"` | `\"true\"` \\| `\"false\"` |\n| `VITE_RPC_URL` | Solana RPC endpoint URL | `WalletProvider.tsx`, `TestWalletWrapper.tsx` | `https://api.devnet.solana.com` | `http://127.0.0.1:8899`, `https://api.devnet.solana.com` |\n| `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK` | Solana cluster name (for wallet-adapter) | `RealWalletProvider.tsx` | `\"devnet\"` | `\"devnet\"` \\| `\"testnet\"` \\| `\"mainnet-beta\"` |\n| `VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID` | Coinflip program address override | `chain.ts`, `verification.ts` | *(from IDL)* | `BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx` |\n| `VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID` | Platform program address override | `chain.ts` (claimPayout) | `85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA` | *(varies per deployment)* |\n\n---\n\n## 3. **Program ID Resolution Strategy**\n\n### **Source Hierarchy**\n1. **VITE_ env vars take precedence** (if set)\n2. **IDL embedded defaults fallback** (if env var not provided)\n\n### **IDL Locations**\n- **Coinflip**: `@rng-utopia/anchor-client` exports `CoinflipIDL` (from `coinflip.json`)\n- **Platform**: `@rng-utopia/anchor-client` exports `PlatformIDL` (from `platform.json`)\n\n### **Code Patterns**\n```typescript\n// chain.ts, line 20-22\nconst COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  import.meta.env.VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID ?? CoinflipIDL.address\n);\n\n// chain.ts, line 445-448\nconst PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  import.meta.env.VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID ?? \n  \"85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA\"\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. **E2E Test Fixtures & Helpers Structure**\n\n### **Dual-Browser Context Fixture** (`e2e/local/fixtures.ts`)\n```typescript\nexport interface DualPlayerFixtures {\n  playerAContext: BrowserContext;          // Player A's isolated browser context\n  playerBContext: BrowserContext;          // Player B's isolated browser context\n  playerAPage: Page;                       // Page in player A's context\n  playerBPage: Page;                       // Page in player B's context\n  playerAKeypair: Keypair;                 // PLAYER_A (from wallets.ts)\n  playerBKeypair: Keypair;                 // PLAYER_B (from wallets.ts)\n  connection: Connection;                  // Shared RPC connection\n}\n```\n\n**Key mechanism**: Uses `addInitScript` to inject `window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__` before page load, allowing `TestWalletWrapper` to construct the correct keypair.\n\n### **Wallet Keypairs** (`e2e/local/helpers/wallets.ts`)\n```typescript\nconst SEED_PLAYER_A = new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xaa);  // Deterministic\nconst SEED_PLAYER_B = new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xbb);  // Deterministic\n\nexport const PLAYER_A = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_PLAYER_A);\nexport const PLAYER_B = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_PLAYER_B);\nexport const LOCAL_RPC_URL = \"http://127.0.0.1:8899\";\n\n// Helper to fund wallets (idempotent)\nexport async function fundTestWallets(rpcUrl, solAmount): Promise<{ \n  playerA: Keypair; \n  playerB: Keypair; \n  connection: Connection \n}>;\n```\n\n### **On-Chain Helpers** (`e2e/local/helpers/on-chain.ts`)\n**Program ID resolution**:\n```typescript\nexport const COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(CoinflipIDL.address);\nexport const PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(PlatformIDL.address);\n```\n\n**Account types & interfaces**:\n- `MatchAccount` — deserialized coinflip match PDA\n- `PlayerProfileAccount` — deserialized player profile PDA\n\n**Assertion helpers**:\n- `assertMatchCreated(connection, creator, expectedTier, expectedSide)`\n- `assertMatchClosed(connection, matchPda)`\n- `assertTreasuryFee(connection, treasury, balanceBefore, entryAmount)`\n- `assertPlayerProfile(connection, wallet, expected)`\n- `assertPlayerProfileDelta(connection, wallet, before, delta)`\n\n**Balance & snapshot helpers**:\n- `snapshotBalance(connection, address)` — capture SOL balance\n- `snapshotPlayerProfile(connection, wallet)` — capture profile stats (returns zeros if not exists)\n- `calculateExpectedFee(entryAmount)` — mirrors on-chain fee logic: `fee = floor(pool * 300 / 10_000)`\n\n### **Localnet Setup** (`e2e/local/helpers/localnet-setup.ts`)\n```typescript\n// Deterministic admin & treasury keypairs\nconst ADMIN = Keypair.fromSeed(new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xdd));\nconst TREASURY = Keypair.fromSeed(new Uint8Array(32).fill(0xcc));\n\n// Initializes both program configs (idempotent)\nexport async function initializeLocalnet(rpcUrl = LOCAL_RPC_URL): Promise<void>;\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. **`.env` Files**\n\n### `.env.devnet` (Current)\n```\nVITE_RPC_URL=https://api.devnet.solana.com\nVITE_SOLANA_NETWORK=devnet\nVITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID=BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\nVITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID=85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA\n```\n\n### `.env.example`\n```\n# Wallet Mode\n# VITE_MOCK_MODE=true\n\n# Solana Configuration\nVITE_RPC_URL=https://api.devnet.solana.com\nVITE_SOLANA_NETWORK=devnet\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. **Vite Configuration** (`vite.config.ts`)\n- **Default port**: 3000\n- **Server host**: `true` (accessible from non-localhost)\n- **Build optimizations**: Manual chunks for react/solana vendor splitting\n- **No special env var handling** — relies on Vite's automatic `VITE_*` exposure\n\n---\n\n## 7. **WalletProvider Initialization Flow**\n\n### **Decision Tree**\n```\nVITE_MOCK_MODE === \"true\"\n  ├─ Yes → MockWalletProvider (no RPC interaction)\n  └─ No\n      ├─ VITE_TEST_WALLET === \"true\"\n      │   └─ TestWalletWrapper (reads window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__)\n      └─ No → RealWalletProvider (UnifiedWallet modal)\n```\n\n### **RPC URL Resolution** (`getRpcUrl()`)\n```typescript\nconst envUrl = import.meta.env?.VITE_RPC_URL ?? undefined;\nreturn envUrl || DEFAULT_RPC_URL;  // DEFAULT_RPC_URL = \"https://api.devnet.solana.com\"\n```\n\n### **Network/Cluster Resolution** (`getCluster()`)\n```typescript\nconst network = import.meta.env?.VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK;\nif (network === \"mainnet-beta\" || network === \"testnet\") return network;\nreturn \"devnet\";  // Default to devnet\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. **Test Wallet System**\n\n### **Flow for E2E Tests**\n1. **Playwright injects keypair seed** via `addInitScript` → `window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__`\n2. **WalletProvider detects** `VITE_TEST_WALLET=true` and renders `TestWalletWrapper`\n3. **TestWalletWrapper reads** `window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__` and creates keypair\n4. **TestWalletProvider** wraps the keypair with signing capability\n5. **Frontend can sign transactions** without modal prompts\n\n### **Key Code** (`test/TestWalletWrapper.tsx`)\n```typescript\nconst keypair = Keypair.fromSeed(new Uint8Array(seed));\nconst rpcUrl = import.meta.env?.VITE_RPC_URL as string | undefined;\nreturn <TestWalletProvider keypair={keypair} rpcUrl={rpcUrl || undefined}>{children}</TestWalletProvider>;\n```\n\n---\n\n## 9. **Visual Regression Setup** (`fixtures.ts` at root of `e2e/`)\n\n**Key fixture**: `stablePage` extends Playwright's test:\n- **Deterministic randomness** via seeded Mulberry32 PRNG (seed=42)\n- **Frozen Date.now()** to 2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\n- **Disabled CSS/SVG animations** to ensure pixel-perfect snapshots\n- **Console error detection** — fails test if errors logged\n- **Network idle enforcement** — waits for all requests to settle\n\n---\n\n## 10. **Summary: What You Need for Devnet Validation Module**\n\n### **Environment Variables to Validate**\n1. `VITE_RPC_URL` — must be reachable, valid HTTPS/HTTP URL\n2. `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK` — must be one of: `devnet` | `testnet` | `mainnet-beta`\n3. `VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID` — must be a valid Solana address (58 chars, base58)\n4. `VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID` — must be a valid Solana address\n\n### **On-Chain Validation to Implement**\n1. **RPC health check** — `connection.getHealth()` or `getLatestBlockhash()`\n2. **Program deployment check** — fetch program account at `VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID` and `VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID`\n3. **Keypoint config check** — verify coinflip & platform configs initialized (PDAs derivable)\n4. **Treasury check** — treasury wallet set and accessible\n\n### **Fallback Chain**\n- Program IDs: VITE_ env vars → IDL embedded defaults\n- RPC URL: VITE_RPC_URL → `https://api.devnet.solana.com`\n- Network: VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK → `devnet`\n\n---\n\n## File Paths (Absolute)\n\n1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.local.config.ts` — Local E2E config\n2. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/.env.devnet` — Devnet env file\n3. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts` — Visual regression fixture\n4. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/fixtures.ts` — Dual-player fixture\n5. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/wallets.ts` — Wallet setup\n6. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/on-chain.ts` — On-chain helpers\n7. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/localnet-setup.ts` — Localnet init\n8. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/vite.config.ts` — Vite build config\n9. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/WalletProvider.tsx` — Wallet provider root\n10. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/test/TestWalletWrapper.tsx` — Test wallet wrapper\n11. `/workspaces/rng-uto